+## Module `duh.kernel.engine`
+
+### `class EngineConfig(model: str = '', fallback_model: str | None = None, max_fallback_retries: int = 1, system_prompt: str | list[str] = '', tools: list[Any] = <factory>, thinking: dict[str, Any] | None = None, tool_choice: str | dict[str, Any] | None = None, max_turns: int = 1000, max_cost: float | None = None, cwd: str = '.', trifecta_acknowledged: bool = False, auto_memory: bool = False)`
+
+Purpose: immutable-ish configuration bundle for one `Engine` session.
+
+Example:
+
+```python
+from duh.kernel.engine import EngineConfig
+
+cfg = EngineConfig(model="stub-model", system_prompt="hi")
+print(cfg.model)
+```
+
+### `class Engine(deps: Deps, config: EngineConfig | None = None, session_store: SessionStore | None = None, structured_logger: StructuredLogger | None = None, **kwargs: Any)`
+
+Purpose: own session lifecycle, message history, costs, compaction, and execution flow for a conversation.
+
+Parameters:
+
+- `deps: Deps`
+- `config: EngineConfig | None = None`
+- `session_store: SessionStore | None = None`
+- `structured_logger: StructuredLogger | None = None`
+- `**kwargs: Any`
+
+Exceptions:
+
+- may raise trifecta-related errors during initialization if session capabilities are unsafe without acknowledgement.
+
+Example:
+
+```python
+from duh.kernel.deps import Deps
+from duh.kernel.engine import Engine, EngineConfig
+
+engine = Engine(deps=Deps(), config=EngineConfig(model="stub-model"))
+print(engine.model)
+```
+
